 Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas de Wotton was born in 1400, in Chester, Cheshire, England, his father, John Wotton, was 44 and his mother, Englesia Dymoke, was 28. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Joan Corbie. He died on 14 September 1448, in Somme, Picardie, France, at the age of 48."},"et":{"1400–14 September 1448":"1400–14. september 1448","1400–1448":"1400–1448","1402–1437":"1402–1437","1404–1454":"1404–1454","1428–1483":"1428–1483","1434–1491":"1434–1491","1357–1408":"1357–1408","1372–1408":"1372–1408","8 March 1408":"8. märts 1408","1483":"1483","Abt 1434":"umbes 1434","1372":"1372","1491":"1491","1404":"1404","1437":"1437","1448":"1448","1402":"1402","1357":"1357","1434":"1434","1400":"1400","1454":"1454","1408":"1408","1428":"1428","14 September 1448":"14. september 1448","Widworthy, Devonshire, England":"Widworthy, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Chester, Cheshire, England":"Blacon, Chester, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Boughton, Malherbe, Kent, England":"Boughton under Blean, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Widworthy, Devon, England":"Widworthy, Devon, England"},"fi":{"1400–14 September 1448":"1400–14. syyskuuta 1448","1400–1448":"1400–1448","1402–1437":"1402–1437","1404–1454":"1404–1454","1428–1483":"1428–1483","1434–1491":"1434–1491","1357–1408":"1357–1408","1372–1408":"1372–1408","8 March 1408":"8. maaliskuuta 1408","1483":"1483","Abt 1434":"noin 1434","1372":"1372","1491":"1491","1404":"1404","1437":"1437","1448":"1448","1402":"1402","1357":"1357","1434":"1434","1400":"1400","1454":"1454","1408